comments.body:
@mehulgogri are you a rhel8/centos8 stream user? I think the latest skopeo should be landing in the next upcoming release of rhel 8.6.0 sometime soon. It will likely land on centos8 stream before the rhel release.

rhel 7 (and centos 7) are not getting updates anymore for skopeo and related tools, so best bet would be to build from source or use the container image as others have mentioned here.

Don't really know about SLES. Might be worth checking with the package maintainers there?

@lsm5 @vrothberg @mtrmac Thanks for your responses.
I do not want to create a docker dependency in my project. For time being I will manually create the skopeo bin and unblock myself, till we find some better solution to install new version of skopeo in the operating systems that we support for my project.

Question: Once I have created a skopeo bin file in SLES15 operating system, can I use this same bin file in any other operating system to install skopeo? or should I create a separate skopeo bin file on each operating system?
